Package cellery

Cellery v0.1

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Automaton
    Automaton is an object that can evolve Cells contained within a CellArray2D or CellArray1D.
    Automaton1D
    Automaton1D is a 1 dimensional extension of CellularAutomata
    Automaton2D
    Automaton2D is a 2 dimensional extension of Automaton
    BinaryAutomaton1D
    A 2-state Automaton1D
    BinaryAutomaton2D
    A 2-state Automaton2D
    Cell
    Cells are objects with two states: dead or alive.
    CellArray1D
    CellArray1D is a 1-d array of Cell objects which can kill or resurrect Cells and retrieve neighborhoods about individual Cells.
    CellArray2D
    A CellArray2D is a two dimensional grid of Cells.
    CellerySeeds
    Static methods for generating initial conditions for 2-state Automata.
    ElementaryAutomaton
    A 2-state Automaton1D controlled by Stephen Wolfram's 256 Elementary Automation Rules.
